ted Anomalies\n1. **Node Level Anomalies**\n   - **Node Filesystem Usage Rate**: `aiops-k8s-05` showed a dramatic increase in `node_filesystem_usage_rate` from 25.2 to 66.64 with a change ratio of 0.9023.\n   - **Node CPU Usage Rate**: `aiops-k8s-01` exhibited a significant increase in `node_cpu_usage_rate` from 25.74 to 31.81, with the P99 change showing an even larger increase to 64.45.\n\n2. **Pod Level Anomalies**\n   - **Pod CPU Usage**: `redis-cart-0` CPU usage showed a P99 decrease. While this doesn't seem directly alarming, it's important to monitor.\n\n3. **Service Level Anomalies**\n   - **`rrt_max` Metric**: \n     - **Payment Service**: Payment service pod `paymentservice-0` showed an rrt_max P99 increase from 10,500.08 to 41,353.2.\n     - **Shipping Service**: Similarly, the shipping service pod `shippingservice-0` displayed an increase from 8,640.37 to 28,231.9.\n\n4. **TiDB IO Utilization**:\n   - **IO Utilization** for `tidb-tikv` displayed changes, though the median remained zero.\n\n### Hypotheses\nBelow are our hypotheses surrounding the root causes, based on the metrics and anomalies detected:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"node_filesystem_usage_rate\",\n    \"node_cpu_usage_rate\",\n    \"pod_cpu_usage\",\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"io_util\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"Significant increase in filesystem usage rate, indicating potential disk saturation or file system overload.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Filesystem usage rate changed from 25.2 to 66.64 with a change ratio of 0.9023.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-01\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increase in CPU usage rate, possibly indicating resource exhaustion or overload.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"CPU usage rate increased from 25.74 to 31.81.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"paymentservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"High rrt_max indicating potential latency or performance bottleneck.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max P99 increased from 10,500.08 to 41,353.2.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"High rrt_max, potential latency issues or service slowdown.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max P99 increased from 8,640.37 to 28,231.9.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThese hypotheses represent potential areas contributing to the observed fault, with performance and resource metrics primarily indicating probable bottlenecks or component overloads. Further investigation is recommended to narrow down root causes or additional impacts."}
